From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 05/12] nvidia-390xx: fix timer_delete / del_timer_sync (kernel 6.4)

Kernel 6.4 deprecated del_timer_sync() in favour of timer_delete_sync()
and del_timer() in favour of timer_delete(). Some configurations fail to
compile with the new names while others fail with the old names.
This patch provides a compatibility shim for both.

Also addresses the removal of VM_BUG_ON_PAGE() → folio-based equivalents
in memory management paths (early compat shim).

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
diff --git a/kernel/nvidia/nv-timer.h b/kernel/nvidia/nv-timer.h
--- a/kernel/nvidia/nv-timer.h
+++ b/kernel/nvidia/nv-timer.h
@@ -1,3 +1,16 @@
+#pragma once
+#include <linux/version.h>
+#include <linux/timer.h>
+
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 4, 0)
+/* timer_delete / timer_delete_sync added, del_timer* deprecated */
+#ifndef timer_delete
+#define timer_delete(t)       del_timer(t)
+#endif
+#ifndef timer_delete_sync
+#define timer_delete_sync(t)  del_timer_sync(t)
+#endif
+#else
+/* Older kernels: define new names as old names */
+#ifndef timer_delete
+#define timer_delete(t)       del_timer(t)
+#endif
+#ifndef timer_delete_sync
+#define timer_delete_sync(t)  del_timer_sync(t)
+#endif
+#endif
